  "body": "## About AnchorBrowser\n\nAnchorBrowser is a cloud browser platform built specifically for AI agents. It provides managed Chromium instances with stealth capabilities, enabling agents to automate any website reliably.\n\n**Key capabilities:**\n- \ud83c\udf10 Connect via Puppeteer/Playwright over WebSocket/CDP \u2014 zero infrastructure\n- \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Custom Chromium with stealth \u2014 verified as human traffic by Cloudflare\n- \ud83d\udd10 Handles SSO, MFA, session cookies across automation runs\n- \u26a1 Native MCP server for Claude, GPT, Cursor, and other AI tools\n- \ud83d\ude80 Batch sessions: up to 5,000 concurrent browsers\n- \ud83c\udfe2 Enterprise: SOC2, ISO27001, GDPR, HIPAA compliant\n\n**Quick start:**\n```javascript\n// Create a session and connect with Puppeteer\nconst session = await fetch('https://api.anchorbrowser.io/v1/sessions', {\n  method: 'POST', headers: { 'anchor-api-key': 'YOUR_KEY' }\n}).then(r => r.json());\n\nconst browser = await puppeteer.connect({\n  browserWSEndpoint: session.cdp_url\n});\n```\n\n\ud83d\udd17 **Website:** https://anchorbrowser.io | **Docs:** https://docs.anchorbrowser.io\n> This PR follows the guidelines in [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/langchain-ai/langchain/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n---\n*Added to section: `## Additional resources`*",
